							</author>
							<decoNote type="other">
								<locus n="120r, 164v"/>A pen and ink design enclosing the parashah sign.</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="other">
								<locus n="217v"/>An ornamental design in colours.</decoNote>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the end of 16-17th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex.</support>
								<extent rend="visible">224 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>217</height>
										<width>149</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>167</height>
										<width>105</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>224 folios (+2 paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>23 quires of 10 leaves each, with quires 1-3, 5, 17 and 23 imperfect.</p>
									<p>Quires signed with Hebrew letters and Arabic words on the upper margin of the first page, and also on the lower margin of the last page.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Lacunae after folios: 1, 2, 11, 18, 29, 165, 224.</p>
									<p>Visible marks of water-damage.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="21" writtenLines="21">
									<p>Biblical verses are given in square characters.</p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
